p: No live virus was detected in saliva expectorates of mosquitoes fed on blood meals containing QML22 7, 10 or 14 days post-feeding. This was in contrast to mosquitoes fed on blood meals containing QML16, which resulted in 16% (4/25) and 28% (7/25) of saliva samples containing virus at day 10 and 14Â dpi, respectively. The titres of DENV in these samples reached a maximum of 1250 CCID 50/mosquito.
